text: Tang Enbo (1898-1959) was a Nationalist general in the Republic of China. Along with Hu Zongnan and Xue Yue, Tang was one of the Kuomintang generals most respected by the Japanese during the Second Sino-Japanese War. ==Related pages== *Operation Ichi-Go Category:1898 births Category:1959 deaths Category:Chinese generals Category:20th-century Chinese military people
title: Tang Enbo
